{
  "stem": "15721.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Obviously, we would observe every holiday and fast day and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it, it was a joyously Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My parents both understood somehow to, to make Jewish observance exciting and joys and beautiful.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My father had a lovely voice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My mother always collaborated in making sure that the, that the food and the, the appointments of the table were just tip-top.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So the house really had a shine of, of Jewishness about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I've tried to convey this in a different way, because I'm now a reform rabbi, to my own household, my own children and grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I think they, too, know something about-- certainly, our children do-- of the joy of being an observant Jew in a different mode than the one that I was used to from my home.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, he had friends who would come and play the piano.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would have, well, soirees in the house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He loved to sing, especially some stuff from Wagner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father was peculiarly a, an aficionado of, of Wagner operas.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he also knew all of the proper melodic treatments of every one of the, the prayers for every day for Sabbath or holidays, all of the variations.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had been trained by his own father who had been a, a teacher of, of Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I learned a lot, too, because my father used to rehearse at home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I heard the melodies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then there was an orphanage about a half hour's walk away from our home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And another man and he undertook to conduct services there every Friday night for the inmates of that orphanage and for some [INAUDIBLE] him who lived nearby who would come and constitute an adult minyan.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
